===Noun===
'''futurism'''

# An early 20th century avant-garde art movement focused on speed, the mechanical, and the modern.  Took a deeply antagonistic attitude to traditional artistic conventions.  Originated by F.T. Marinetti, among others.
# The study and prediction of possible [[future]]s.

